-- Hits Telecom Plans Two Acquisitions in First Half of 2012
-- B y   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2011-12-20T10:25:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/hits-telecom-plans-two-acquisitions-in-first-half-of-2012.html
  Hits Telecom Holding Company (HITSTELE) , a
Kuwait-based telecommunications provider, plans two acquisitions
in the first half of 2012, Chief Executive Officer Par Eriksson
said yesterday.  “During the first quarter, we will definitely announce an
acquisition in a country in Africa, and then we may announce the
second acquisition in another country in the following
quarter,” he said in a phone interview from  Kuwait City . He did
not give any more information.  Hits Telecom  may also “close another loan in the beginning
of next year” through a combination of local and Asian banks,
Eriksson said. The company said on Dec. 5 it has agreed to a
158.8 million-dinar ($43 million) loan from Swiss-based Global
Emerging Ltd.  Hits Telecom owns company stakes in Saudi Arabia, Spain,
Liberia, Equatorial Guinea, Tanzania and  Democratic Republic  of
Congo, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dahlia Kholaif in Kuwait at 
